elements.title: films starring Judy Ann Santos (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Ploning and Mindanao, films starring Judy Ann Santos (pictured), were the Philippine submissions for Best International Feature Film at the 81st and 93rd Academy Awards, respectively?

elements.title: Bridge Apartments (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that the 32-story Bridge Apartments in New York City were built directly above a 12-lane freeway?

elements.title: Heather Phillips (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that when Heather Phillips made her European debut in Rossini's Bianca e Falliero at the Oper Frankfurt, reviewers agreed that her nuanced coloraturas served to portray Bianca's development?

elements.title: Kuzych v White (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that in the 1951 court case Kuzych v White, on appeal from the British Columbia Court of Appeal, five law lords of the British Judicial Committee ruled in favour of a Communist-led trade union?

elements.title: Godhavn inquiry (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that the Godhavn inquiry found that a psychiatrist gave children the antipsychotic medication chlorprothixene to stop bedwetting – which was neither standard nor validated by contemporary evidence?

elements.title: Mily Treviño-Sauceda (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Mily Treviño-Sauceda, the co-founder of the first national grassroots women's farmworker organization in the United States, the National Alliance of Farmworker Women, was a child farmworker in the 1960s?

elements.title: Napoleonic looting of art (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that during the Napoleonic looting of art, French soldiers destroyed the Venetian state ship, the Bucentaur, and melted down its gold decorations?

elements.title: KNXV-TV (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that the owner of Phoenix's KNXV-TV "[held] a gun to ABC's head" – and it paid off?
